# COPY FROM

`COPY FROM` copies data into a table using the [Postgres `COPY`
protocol](https://www.postgresql.org/docs/14/sql-copy.html).

## Syntax

<div class="highlight">

``` chroma
COPY [INTO] <table_name> [ ( <column> [, ...] ) ] FROM STDIN
[[WITH] ( <option1> [=] <val1> [, ...] ] )]
;
```

be referenced using their order in the table. With a partial column
list, all unreferenced columns will receive their default value.</td>

<td>A single-quoted one-byte character to use as the column delimiter.

columns). To include the <code>QUOTE</code> character itself in column,
wrap the column’s value in the <code>QUOTE</code> character and prefix
all instance of the value you want to literally interpret with the
<code>ESCAPE</code> value. Must be different from

<br />
Default: <code>"</code>.</td>

<tr>

<td><em>For <code>FORMAT CSV</code> only.</em> A single-quoted string

<code>QUOTE</code> character to be parsed literally as part of a

<br />
Default: <code>QUOTE</code>’s value.</td>

<br />
Default: <code>false</code>.</td>

## Details

### Text formatting

As described in the **Text Format** section of [PostgreSQL’s
documentation](https://www.postgresql.org/docs/14/sql-copy.html).

### CSV formatting

As described in the **CSV Format** section of [PostgreSQL’s
documentation](https://www.postgresql.org/docs/14/sql-copy.html) except
that:

- More than one layer of escaped quote characters returns the wrong
  result.

- Quote characters must immediately follow a delimiter to be treated as
  expected.

- Single-column rows containing quoted end-of-data markers (e.g. `"\."`)
  will be treated as end-of-data markers despite being quoted. In
  PostgreSQL, this data would be escaped and would not terminate the
  data processing.

- Quoted null strings will be parsed as nulls, despite being quoted. In
  PostgreSQL, this data would be escaped.

  To ensure proper null handling, we recommend specifying a unique
  string for null values, and ensuring it is never quoted.

- Unterminated quotes are allowed, i.e. they do not generate errors. In
  PostgreSQL, all open unescaped quotation punctuation must have a
  matching piece of unescaped quotation punctuation or it generates an
  error.

## Example

<div class="highlight">

``` chroma
COPY t FROM STDIN WITH (DELIMITER '|');
```

</div>

<div class="highlight">

``` chroma
COPY t FROM STDIN (FORMAT CSV);
```

</div>

<div class="highlight">

``` chroma
COPY t FROM STDIN (DELIMITER '|');
```

</div>

## Privileges

The privileges required to execute this statement are:

- `USAGE` privileges on the schema containing the table.
- `INSERT` privileges on the table.

## Limits

You can only copy up to 1 GiB of data at a time. If you need this limit
increased, please [chat with our
team](http://materialize.com/convert-account/).
